node.text: Welcome to “An Astronaut’s Guide to Surviving on Earth” with @Sanvellohealth. Mental health comes with a lot of stigma, but it shouldn’t. Taking care of my mental health was part of the mission in space, and it should be part of the mission here on Earth. Stay tuned for more in this series, and download Sanvello to get all of the support you need to help improve your mental health—on your terms.

node.title: An Astronaut’s Guide to Mental Health

node.text: Loneliness, sadness… we talk about these feelings a lot during the holidays—especially this year—but those feelings can happen any time of year to any type of person. The good news is there are proven ways to move through those feelings and feel better. If you’ve ever struggled with isolation, I know the feeling. That’s why I’m partnering with @SanvelloHealth: it’s an app with day-by-day guides on how to feel better, tools to get you through tough moments, plus therapy and coaching. We’ve got a few things cooking, but if you need help now, download Sanvello. It’s private, it’s confidential, and it can help. #SanvelloPartner

node.text: I’m excited to join @offoutdoors and @happy_camper_live to help bring summer camp to your backyard. I’ll be teaching you and your family how to spot planets, stars and satellites with just your own eyes and a little bit of imagination. Stargazing is a fun outdoor activity the whole family can do together at night – just make sure to remember to first apply OFF! Deep Woods® spray for long lasting protection from pesky biting bugs that might try to get in on the fun too! Check out the link in my bio for more. #BackyardSummerCamp #ad

We will #neverforget

node.text:
When I was in space I kept a log, and over the course of a year I probably wrote in it some 150 times. 

Why? 

Well partially because it’s nice to have a record of events, but also because journaling helps you process. When you’re stressed or burned out, even the basics can feel overwhelming. 

Download @SanvelloHealth and check out my latest video with them — I’ll walk you through the basics of keeping a log, and why it works. 

We’re living through what we can hope is a once-in-a-lifetime event. Now’s the time to write things down. ✨📓 ✨

node.text:
It’s not a mission without proper nutrition. 

If you want to know what fueled me on four space flights and three expeditions to the International Space Station, or what the special dietary requirements are for astronauts, hop over to Facebook Live @americanpistachios this Friday (9/3) at 10AM PT for a conversation with Scott Smith, NASA’s head of space nutrition #partner. 

Scott’s an interesting guy whose work extends from the outer posts of Antarctica to outer space. I know you’ll enjoy it. 

For complete info go to fridayfuelup.com 🚀

node.text:
Too many people are still reluctant to seek support for their mental health, but it doesn’t have to be that way. 

In space, taking care of our mental health was just part of the mission. That’s why I’m partnering with @sanvellohealth. Not everything in space is rocket science, but when it was, I trusted the rocket scientists. Same goes for taking care of your mental wellbeing. 

You can try to hack it on your own, but you’re gonna feel a whole lot better sooner if you turn to the experts at @sanvellohealth. Whether you want to use tools on your own, work with a coach or therapist, or just join a community that gets it, Sanvello can help. 

Download it and see for yourself. #sponsored

Ready for launch? 🚀 

Counting down to liftoff of my latest book, sharing 10 life-changing moments from my path to space and how the lessons I learned can help launch your own goals, career or aspirations in life here on Earth. 

Here’s a sneak peak of my new book cover!

Excited to announce the on sale date is 4/12/22. Countdown clock has begun. 🕰 

Available for pre-order now! 
🚀 Link in bio! 🚀 

#booklaunch #yearinspace #astronaut

node.text:
Congratulations to @richardbranson & @virgingalactic on today’s historic test flight—launching a new era in space tourism!

node.text:
One of the great things about being an astronaut and flying in space was being a part of something greater than oneself.

Same holds true about being a U.S. Citizen. Happy #FourthOfJuly!
